KATSINA – National Hajj Commission of Nigeria NAHCON, has expressed satisfaction with the facilities on the ground at the Katsina state pilgrims welfare board. Alhaji Usman Aliyu Shamaki, NAHCON Director, Inspectorate and Compliance, Abuja made this assertion shortly after inspecting facilities at state pilgrims board headquarters in Katsina on Tuesday. Shamaki noted that the inspection of the facilities have become necessary to ensure the early preparations for the hopeful Hajj 2022 exercise. Hajj 2022: NAHCON Urges Pilgrims Boards To Reengineer Operations Lagos Pledges Support For NAHCON On Its PPP Initiative Drive He said the inspection committee would also peruse the acts establishing each state board and make necessary recommendations where applicable to ensure the success of the Hajj exercise. Shamaki who is the team leader commended the Katsina State Pilgrims Welfare Board for it’s resilience in providing desired facilities for the smooth operations of Hajj exercise for it’s pilgrims in the state. Alhaji Suleiman Nuhu Kuki, the state pilgrims board Executive Director, in his address, said the board was established vide Katsina State law No 1 of 1988 and mandated to make necessary arrangements for the smooth pilgrimage and well being of pilgrims registered under the board. He said all structures at the board’s headquarters were provided by the state government, while some other facilities are provided by NAHCON under the development levy scheme to make its work easier and enhance the comfort of the pilgrims. Kuki however assured all state intending pilgrims who willingly role over their deposit of guaranteed slot, adding that, the annual pilgrims education and enlightenment programme would soon commence throughout the state to make the exercise a success in the state. POLL “Very soon also, we shall organize the second annual retreat to enhance the capacity building of staff and convene the stakeholders meeting of all agencies involved in the conduct of Hajj to chart a way forward”, he concluded.